  {
    "title": "Spiralo",
    "url": "https://maps.secondlife.com/secondlife/Caeshu/125/118/1471/?title=Spiralo&img=https%3A%2F%2Flecs-destinations-secondlife-com.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fimg%2F24879%2F60142bb2ea150265370833.jpg&msg=%E2%80%9CSpiralo%E2%80%9D+is+a+virtual+cultural+complex+produced+by+the+noise-classical+music+project+%27Tia+Rungray%27.+The+space+will+include+a+sound+installation+hall%2C+a+gallery%2C+a+caf%C3%A9%2C+and+a+shopping+floor.%0D%0AThe+name+%22Spiralo%22+means+%22spiral%22+in+Esperanto%2C+and+the+name+comes+from+the+fact+that+the+floors+are+arranged+in+a+spiral+pattern%2C+inspired+by+the+image+of+everyday+life+and+art+blending+together+in+virtual+life.+The+idea+is+to+make+it+easier+to+enjoy+high-quality+art+activities+in+Second+Life+and+to+make+visitors+more+aware+of+their+close+relationship+to+life.+It+functions+to+make+everyday+activities+such+as+watching%2C+listening%2C+dressing%2C+talking+and+photography+more+artistic.+It+offers+you+a+way+to+enjoy+the+time+and+space+in+which+you+can+relax+in+everyday+life.+As+a+cultural+hub+for+contemporary+art+in+Second+Life%2C+%E2%80%9CSpiralo%E2%80%9D+hopes+to+continue+to+create+a+cultural+scene.",
    "thumb": "https://lecs-destinations-secondlife-com.s3.amazonaws.com/img/24879/60142bb24bd40631915146.jpg",
    "desc": "“Spiralo” is a virtual cultural complex produced by the noise-classical music project 'Tia Rungray'. The space will include a sound installation hall, a gallery, a café, and a shopping floor.\nThe name \"Spiralo\" means \"spiral\" in Esperanto, and the name comes from the fact that the floors are arranged in a spiral pattern, inspired by the image of everyday life and art blending together in virtual life. The idea is to make it easier to enjoy high-quality art activities in Second Life and to make visitors more aware of their close relationship to life. It functions to make everyday activities such as watching, listening, dressing, talking and photography more artistic. It offers you a way to enjoy the time and space in which you can relax in everyday life. As a cultural hub for contemporary art in Second Life, “Spiralo” hopes to continue to create a cultural scene."
  },
